nrelated."],"variants":[{"name":"Eleanor","meanings":["From an Old French respelling of the Old Provençal name <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Ellen Rocliffe was born in 1350, in England, United Kingdom as the daughter of Sir Bryan Roclyffe and Mrs Roclyffe. She had at least 1 son with John Ingleby. She died in 1400, in her hometown, at the age of 50."},"et":{"1350–1400":"1350–1400","1355–Male":"1355–Surnud","1378–1420":"1378–1420","1315–Male":"1315–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1315":"1315","1400":"1400","1378":"1378","1355":"1355","1420":"1420","about 1378":"umbes 1378","1350":"1350","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Ripley, Yorkshire, England":"Ripley, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"1350–1400":"1350–1400","1355–Male":"1355–Kuollut","1378–1420":"1378–1420","1315–Male":"1315–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1315":"1315","1400":"1400","1378":"1378","1355":"1355","1420":"1420","about 1378":"noin 1378","1350":"1350","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Ripley, Yorkshire, England":"Ripley, Yorkshire, England"},"fr":{"1350–1400":"1350–1400","1355–Male":"1355–Décédé","1378–1420":"1378–1420","1315–Male":"1315–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1315":"1315","1400":"1400","1378":"1378","1355":"1355","1420":"1420","about 1378":"environ 1378","1350":"1350","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Ripley, Yorkshire, England":"Ripley, Everwyck, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Ellen Rocliffe est née en 1350, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, fille de Sir Bryan Roclyffe et Mrs Roclyffe. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec John Ingleby. Elle est décéd